public class InvalidExitValueException

    Thrown by class Process2 if the child process exit value is unexpected.
    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
    See Also:
    Process2.checkExitValue(Collection), Process2.waitForThenCheckExitValue(long, Collection), Serialized Form

      • InvalidExitValueException

        public InvalidExitValueException(int exitValue,
                         Collection<Integer> validExitValueCollection,
                         Throwable optCause,
                         String format,
                         Object... optArgArr)
        Constructor. The message, as specified by parameters format and optArgArr has a suffix appended with additional details about actual vs. allowed exit values. The message need not specify these details.

        Example format: "Failed to run external filter command: %s" Example optArgArr: (filter command arguments)

        Parameters:
        exitValue -
        • actual exit value from child process
        • Accessible via getExitValue()
        validExitValueCollection -
        • non-empty collection of expected (or valid) child process exit values
        • Must not be empty or contain null values
        • Must not contain the actual exit value from parameter exitValue
        • This collection is copied
        optCause -
        • optional underlying cause of this exception that is passed directory to superclass constructor
        • May be null
        • Access via Throwable.getCause()
        • The placement of this argument compared to the other constructor may appear odd. This is necessary as parameters format and optArgArr form a pair, where (i) optArgArr is varargs, and (ii) both are passed directly to String.format(String, Object...).
        format -
        • passed directly to String.format(String, Object...)
        • must not be null, empty, or only whitespace
        optArgArr - optional list of arguments to pass directly to String.format(String, Object...)
        Throws:
        NullPointerException -
        • if validExitValueCollection is null or contains null elements
        • if format is null
        IllegalArgumentException -
        • if validExitValueCollection is empty
        • if format is empty or only whitespace
        • if validExitValueCollection contains exitValue
